JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 49
IS  - 3
SP  - 403
EP  - 409
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Lancaster and Nickell (1980) have argued that in the proportional hazard model the effects of time dependence (true duration dependence) and unobserved sample heterogeneity (spurious duration dependence) cannot be distinguished. We show that both effects can be distinguished if the model allows for observed explanatory variables in the hazard. We also discuss the application of our result to practical situations.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297364
ER  - 



