AB  - In a recent article, Aneuryn-Evans and Deaton propose asymptotic formulae for analysing Monte Carlo studies of the Cox statistics for testing non-nested hypotheses. This note shows the invalidity of those formulae by demonstrating that, in general, the Cox statistics do not have a singular joint asymptotic distribution.
